Apply non-linear easing to hero scroll exit for dramatic 'peels away' feel.

## Current state
- Hero scrolls away with linear 1:1 scroll ratio
- Clip-path animates but feels mechanical

## Desired behavior
- Non-linear scroll motion (ease-out or custom bezier)
- Hero 'resists' initially then accelerates away
- Or: hero moves faster than scroll initially, creating 'peeling' effect
- Scroll feels intentional and designed, not default browser behavior

## Implementation options

### Option 1: Lenis + scroll-linked animation
```javascript
// Custom easing on scroll-linked transforms
lenis.on('scroll', ({ progress }) => {
  const eased = easeOutCubic(progress);
  hero.style.transform = `translateY(${eased * -100}vh)`;
});
```

### Option 2: CSS scroll-timeline with easing
```css
@keyframes hero-exit {
  from { transform: translateY(0); }
  to { transform: translateY(-100vh); }
}
.hero {
  animation: hero-exit linear;
  animation-timeline: scroll();
  animation-timing-function: cubic-bezier(0.16, 1, 0.3, 1);
}
```

### Option 3: GSAP ScrollTrigger
```javascript
gsap.to('.hero', {
  yPercent: -100,
  ease: 'power2.out',
  scrollTrigger: { scrub: true }
});
```

## Acceptance
- [ ] Hero scroll-away feels 'designed' not default
- [ ] Motion has clear easing curve (not linear)
- [ ] Coordinates with mask exit animation
- [ ] Performance: no jank on scroll
- [ ] reduced-motion: falls back to simpler animation

Create custom Ghost storage adapter that optimizes images on upload using Sharp.

## What this does
When user uploads image via Ghost editor:
1. Intercept upload
2. Generate optimized webp + responsive sizes
3. Store all versions
4. Return paths for Ghost to use in srcset

## Storage adapter location
```
/var/www/ghost/content/adapters/storage/optimized-local/
├── index.js
├── package.json
└── README.md
```

## Implementation
```javascript
const LocalStorageBase = require('ghost-storage-base');
const sharp = require('sharp');
const path = require('path');
const fs = require('fs-extra');

class OptimizedLocalStorage extends LocalStorageBase {
  constructor(config) {
    super();
    this.storagePath = config.storagePath || '/content/images/';
    this.sizes = config.sizes || [600, 1000, 1600, 2000];
    this.quality = config.quality || 82;
  }

  async save(image) {
    const targetDir = this.getTargetDir();
    const targetFilename = this.getUniqueFileName(image);
    const basePath = path.join(this.storagePath, targetDir);

    await fs.ensureDir(basePath);

    // Save original
    const originalPath = path.join(basePath, targetFilename);
    await fs.copy(image.path, originalPath);

    // Generate webp version
    const webpPath = originalPath.replace(/\.(jpg|jpeg|png)$/i, '.webp');
    await sharp(image.path)
      .webp({ quality: this.quality })
      .toFile(webpPath);

    // Generate responsive sizes
    for (const width of this.sizes) {
      const sizePath = path.join(basePath, 'size', `w${width}`);
      await fs.ensureDir(sizePath);

      await sharp(image.path)
        .resize(width, null, { withoutEnlargement: true })
        .webp({ quality: this.quality })
        .toFile(path.join(sizePath, targetFilename.replace(/\.(jpg|jpeg|png)$/i, '.webp')));
    }

    return `/${targetDir}/${targetFilename}`;
  }

  // ... exists(), delete(), read() methods
}
```

## Ghost configuration
```json
// config.production.json
{
  "storage": {
    "active": "optimized-local",
    "optimized-local": {
      "storagePath": "/var/www/ghost/content/images",
      "sizes": [600, 1000, 1600, 2000],
      "quality": 82
    }
  }
}
```

## Deployment
1. Copy adapter to content/adapters/storage/
2. npm install in adapter directory
3. Update Ghost config
4. Restart Ghost

## CI/CD integration
- Adapter code in repo under ghost/adapters/
- Deploy script copies to correct location
- Config managed via environment or config file

## Acceptance
